	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />sevast: Yes, the game is very gimmicky, not all that fun, and the Uforce performs at it's typical low standards.  I don't want to see it emulated because it's a fun game, though, I want it emulated because there's really no other way that the general public will be able to play this game.
<br />
<br />pragma: Maybe I'm misunderstanding you, but for this game, you'd have to do more than just map the keys into a "Uforce layout."  You can't get any response in this game, on a real system or in an emulator, using the regular controller.  I don't know what it is, but there's something unique about the Uforce that makes it impossible to play this game without it.  I like your idea of a seperate "Uforce window," but you're right, some of the games on this cart require you to use two hands.
<br />
<br />I spoke with rbudrick about this a little while back, and he suggested skipping emulation all together and creating a way to connect a real Uforce directly to the PC.  It's a good idea, but I'd prefer emulation, if possible, since the number of Uforce owners out there is pretty limited.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
